cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with creating a dataset for autonomous vehicle perception using synthetic images and LiDAR data. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for image processing and object detection, robotics (cs.RO) for autonomous vehicle navigation, machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) for training object detection networks, and computer graphics (cs.GR) for creating the synthetic environment. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.RO, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.GR.
